      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "**Key features / functional groups**\n- **Two cationic nitrogens**: a **diazabicyclic/piperazine-like** ring shown as `[NH+]1... [NH+] ...CC1` \u2192 **dicationic at physiological pH** (strong basic centers).\n- **Amide linker**: `Ar\u2013NH\u2013C(=O)\u2013CH\u2013` (anilide/urea-like motif). Amide N is not basic; carbonyl is H-bond acceptor.\n- **Multiple aromatic/hydrophobic domains**\n  - One **dimethyl-substituted phenyl** ring (`Cc1cccc(C)c1\u2013`)\n  - A **diaryl (biphenyl-like) group** with **two fluorophenyl rings**: `(c2ccc(F)cc2)c2ccc(F)cc2`\n- **Flexible hydrophobic spacer**: `CCCC( diaryl )` attached to the cationic ring \u2192 provides **reach/length** and conformational adaptability.",
