    },
    {
      "step_id": "846edf2e",
      "step_index": 6,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "## 3) Mechanistic basis (how it would interact with hERG)\nMechanistically, typical high-risk blockers bind in the **central cavity** of hERG:\n- The **protonated amine(s)** can provide **electrostatic/cation\u2013\u03c0 interactions** and help orient the ligand.\n- The **diaryl group** can stack or interact hydrophobically with **aromatic residues** in the cavity (notably the well-known aromatic lining that drives many hERG interactions).\n- The **flexible chain** allows the ligand to adopt a \u201cplug-like\u201d conformation that **occludes K\u207a conduction**.",
