      "content": "## 5) Verification / uncertainty check (contradictions, alternatives)\n- **Potential counterargument:** The molecule is **dicationic**, which can reduce membrane permeation and sometimes lowers functional blockade in intact-cell formats.\n  - **Why this likely doesn\u2019t overturn the call:** The structure also has **very large hydrophobic aromatic mass**, which can partially offset polarity for membrane association, and the **pharmacophore match to known hERG-binding motifs is strong**.\n- **3D dependence caveat:** Exact potency depends on whether the ring + linker places the diaryl group optimally in the cavity; however, the **flexible butyl tether** makes a compatible conformation more likely rather than less.",
